text:
Hell all, my name is Eden Abate. I am a entrepreneur and creative director with a financial consulting background. I work with numerous young creatives and entrepreneurs across Sub-Saharan Africa. I am also the owner of a small sustainable textile manufacturing company in Addis Ababa Ethiopia. I.e We only work with natural fibers and textiles.

Currently involved in five COVID projects.

1. Production of face-masks and medical gear  for donation. Working on this in partnership with fashion designers association and other small scale manufactures. 100 designers together. My manufacturing company has been doing research and testing for material the past couple of weeks. We will start production this coming week and donate as a group.
2. Ventilators - Assisting the NERD team with their production of ventilators in country.
3. Creative directing three videos currently being produced with influencers and doctors.
4. Working on Illustrations in partnership with digital artists in Addis.
5. Developing recipes with chefs and bakers that can be given to doctors and volunteers focusing on ease of production, nutrition and  immunity boosting ingredients. 

I am happy to share any details on the above projects, my manufacturing company as well the network of creatives I work with. I am more than ready to help our country get through this!

text:
Hello all, good to be here. Hope all is with you. My name is Hadra Ahmed, Ethiopian based freelance journalist working with local and international media outlets. I also run a media and communications company, Nubia. We work on Media, communications, technology consultancy; TV, radio, digital productions; public relations; strategy and etc.
We are currently working on various videos for awareness with doctors mainly but also have artists and citizens lined up for more work. We are also supporting a volunteer group #doingmypart and so far we have:
·        Set up hand washing stations in various areas of Kazanchis. We plan to do the same in Megenagna ane Piazza. Also provide soap for those who already set up stations.
·        Donated groceries to households of the vulnerable, low income families and elderly
·        Currently finalising to distribute groceries and sanitary materials including masks and gloves to street sweepers
·        Create awareness materials such as posters, videos and etc.
Our team and resources are available for anyone who would like to contribute and work together from Addis.
Cheers, H.
